sentences.sContent: Shelley and Byron were the sons of aristocrats while Keats was the son of an innkeeper.
sentences.sContent_eng: Shelley and Byron were the sons of aristocrats while Keats was the son of an innkeeper.
sentences.sCn: 雪莱和拜伦是贵族子弟，而济慈只是一个旅馆老板的儿子。

trans.tranOther: someone who owns or manages an inn
